<b>Axalto</b> was a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../957/59957.xml">
smart card</link> manufacturer with over 4,500 employees in 60 countries, one of the world's leading providers of microprocessor cards (<company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../363/250363.xml">
Gartner</link></company>
, 2005) and also a major supplier of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../633/220633.xml">
point of sale</link> terminals.<p>

In June 2006, Axalto merged with rival <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../712/8605712.xml">
Gemplus International</link></company>
 to form <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../110/4981110.xml">
Gemalto</link></company>
.</p>
<p>

