<sec>
<st>
History</st>
<p>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Formerly, Axalto was the Smart Card and Terminal Department of <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../876/461876.xml">
Schlumberger</link></company>
. </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

After Schlumberger purchased Sema, the Smart Card and Terminal Department became a part of SchlumbergerSema. </entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

And then after Schlumberger sold Sema to <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../299/895299.xml">
Atos Origin</link></company>
, the Smart Card and Terminal Department became Axalto.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

In 2004, Axalto had its <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../879/63879.xml">
initial public offering</link>.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

On December 7, 2005, it announced its <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../769/20769.xml">
merger</link> plan with main competitor Gemplus, to create <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../110/4981110.xml">
Gemalto</link></company>
.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

On May 19, 2006, the European Commission approves the merger between Axalto and Gemplus</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

On June 2, 2006, the new company, Gemalto, is officially created</entry>
</list>
</p>

